1.
module Sing where
  fstString :: [Char] -> [Char]
  fstString x = x ++ " in the rain"
  sndString :: [Char] -> [Char]
  sndString x = x  ++ " over the rainbow"
  sing = if (x > y) then fstString x else sndString y
    where x = "Singin"
          y = "Somewhere"

2.
Now that it’s fixed, make a minor change and make it sing the
other song. If you’re lucky, you’ll end up with both songs stuck
in your head!

3. -- arith3broken.hs
module Arith3Broken where
  main :: IO ()
  main = do
   print $ 1 + 2
   putStrLn "10"
   print (negate (-1))
   print ((+) 0 blah) where
     blah = negate 1
